                            <comment id="12536183" author="mcculls" created="Fri, 19 Oct 2007 11:30:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;note, as a temporary workaround you can use:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;          &amp;lt;manifestLocation&amp;gt;${basedir}/META-INF&amp;lt;/manifestLocation&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;which will place the manifest in the right directory.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12536187" author="mcculls" created="Fri, 19 Oct 2007 11:46:22 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Fixed in trunk, and deployed new snapshot.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12552228" author="mcculls" created="Sun, 16 Dec 2007 16:07:51 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;d like to get all resolved defects verified before releasing the 1.1.0 version of the bundleplugin - so I&apos;d really appreciate it if you could check things are still ok with the current snapshot, and if so close off the defect.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks in advance!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12563956" author="mcculls" created="Wed, 30 Jan 2008 10:39:27 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Closing issue, as the 1.2.0 version of the bundleplugin which contains the fix is now released.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
